From 8963c08ae4333b67bfb34d666aa0779e3c208355 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Sep 2025 02:30:52 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP: wifi: ath12k: Fix RCU stall due to missing
 rcu_read_unlock

rcu_read_unlock() is missed for a few error cases in
PPDU stats handler (ath12k_htt_pull_ppdu_stats),
As a reason we see that the thread is entering the
RCU read side sections multiple times without properly
exiting them.

Patch-dependency:0452-0003-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Process-pktlog-buffer-in-various.patch
Patch-work: None
Fixes: 0452-0003-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Process-pktlog-buffer-in-various.patch

Change-Id: I0cf634e8e18d590bf75e6f22c28eb772a07f0357
Signed-off-by: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c
index 53c4d84..1b103b3 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c
@@ -900,6 +900,7 @@ static int ath12k_htt_pull_ppdu_stats(struct ath12k_base *ab,
 		 * and hence %NULL return is possible. Just silently
 		 * discard this message
 		 */
+		rcu_read_unlock();
 		goto exit;
 	}
 
@@ -911,6 +912,7 @@ static int ath12k_htt_pull_ppdu_stats(struct ath12k_base *ab,
 
 	dp_pdev = ath12k_dp_to_dp_pdev(dp, pdev_id - 1);
 	if (!dp_pdev) {
+		rcu_read_unlock();
 		ret = -EINVAL;
 		goto exit;
 	}
-- 
